post_text:
Today's the day - happy Virtual Charter Day 2020! We're going LIVE on Facebook at 11:30AM, and we can't wait for you to join us! Follow these quick instructions to tune in and share our live post with YOUR friends, school Facebook page audience, etc.

Visit our MI Charters Facebook page around 11:30AM, when we'll go LIVE for the big program. We'll wait for about 5 minutes before getting started so everyone can tune in.
Once you find the video on our page, click the "Share" option. Either select "Share Now (Friends)" or to share to your school's Facebook page select "More Options" then "Share to a Page" and select your school's page.
Be sure to have your school swag on, and be ready to post a photo showing it off, along with a message about why you LOVE your charter school, in the comments!

post_text: Participate in the #GEEgottalent Challenges! See the instructions below!
shared_text:
Global Educational Excellence
May 9 at 12:51 PM ·

GEE’s Got Talent

This Spring, any GEE students may compete in weekly competitions. We will have a different competition each week with some prizes up for grabs and bragging rights on the line. Each participant must submit pictures/videos to the following email address; gottalent@gee-edu.com please include your name, academy, and grade level.

Our panel of GEE judges will vote on the submissions and declare the winners on GEE’s Facebook page.
Some of the contests coming your way this Spring include; Trick Shot Challenge, Mascot Art Contest, Choreography Competition, Chess Tournament, Fitness Challenges, and more! #GEEgottalent See below details for Week 1:
May 11 - May 17

Trick Shot Challenge

In its 51st year, the annual America & Me Essay Contest, sponsored by Farm Bureau Insurance Michigan encourages students to submit essays based on the topic "My Personal Michigan Hero".

Central Academy is proud to announce that three of our students were chosen from several thousand other eighth-graders in Michigan for submitting their exceptional essays.

Below are the school winners

1st Place - Asmaa Issa
2nd Place - Rahma Tariq
3rd Place - Islam Nemer

Asmaa Issa will now advance to the state level competition in hopes of being awarded one of the top ten essays in Michigan!!!
Global Educational Excellence Michigan's Charter Schools

Tomorrow, Wednesday May 29th, Central Academy will be participating in Eastern Michigan University Annual Math Facts Challenge for the 4th year. Our students look forward to this event every year. For the past two years, Central Academy has proudly taken home 1st place trophies for Elementary & Middle school and in 2016 we took home the 1st place trophy for Middle school!

Please follow EMU on both Facebook and Instagram throughout the day to track the event and they will be LIVESTREAMING the Finals at 12:30p with the Awards Ceremony to follow!

Please tune in and support our students, cheer for students from your school or just show support; here are the links to EMU's Instagram and Facebook accounts. Go Central!

post_text:
Eastern Michigan University is offering a Computer Science Camp for Middle School girls! Students will explore multiple paths relating to Technology and complete projects using applications such as Lego Robots, Ozobots, and AppInventor. Each girl will be given the opportunity to interact with college students who are studying computer science and female professionals from the industry as well. There will also be a day dedicated to letting the participants demonstrate what they have learned and apply their ideas to a real-world challenge (a Mockathon!) and they will have a field trip to a local IT company.

The camp is a full week and full day, Mon-Fri, 9am-4pm. The cost is $50, financial scholarships available. Parents please sign up your daughter to join this summer. Quick, spots are going fast!

post_text:
Three students from our school have been named local winners in the 50th annual America & Me Essay Contest, sponsored by Farm Bureau Insurance Michigan!!!
The topic for the essay was " My Personal Michigan Hero" where the students shared inspirational stories on how they were influenced by a special someone.

First Place- Shatha Thabata
Second Place- Alizeh Kashif Bari
Third Place- Yasmeen Nemer

Shatha Thabata's first place essay now advances to the state level competition, from which the top ten essays in Michigan will be selected!!!

Congratulations to our winners and all of the students that participated in this contest!
Michigan's Charter Schools Central Michigan University Global Educational Excellence
#charterslead
